		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				I use an odd navigation method for fps games... <br>  <br> the numeric keypad, with: <br> 8 = forward <br> 5 = back <br> 7 = move left <br> 4 = turn left <br> 9 = move right <br> 6 = turn right <br>  <br> all the older fps games allow for that scheme, but some of the newer games (BF1942 and Raven Shield for example) don't. Very annoying... (though I was able to figure out how to edit an ini file to enable it for Raven Shield).  <br>  <br> So, if it's in the HL2 engine, please make sure VTMB supports it... if it's not in the HL2 engine, please yell at valve and get them to put it in and get an updated copy of it <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/4.gif" border="0" alt="grin" hspace="0" vspace="0"> 		

			</td>
