			<td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span> 
			5/12/03 9:45pm 
			<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> RE: Game Mechanics Request: Please allow for &quot;Turn Left&quot; and &quot;Turn Right&quot; keys			
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Wow, I must admit, I have never seen that before. <br>  <br> I am a veteran FPS player (Half Life and related mods for 4 and a half odd years, Unreal Tournament for 2 odd years). I hate the defaultt controls, too inneficient, you usually lose anywhere up to half a second doing something. <br>  <br> I use the WASD keys, along with: <br> E - Jump, right next to my movement keys, I suppose space is not too bad, but is slower, and I have no idea why some people use ctrl. <br> Q - Crouch, right next to movement keys, makes complex manuevers easier to perform. <br>  <br> I also use an inverted mouse, very uncommon, with high mouse sensitivity, even more uncommon. <br> My mouse sensitivity is set at 5.6, whereas most players have their's on 1.3. Again, speed = efficiency. The claims that &quot;but you can't move just a little to nail their head&quot; are complete BS, if you can't move a little with high sensitivity, it's your own fault, I enjoy being able to make acrobatic style movements by flicking my wrist. <br>  <br> Okay okay, it seems I've taken this to the classic shoot-em-up style, and I realise that, but it's what I'm used to. I do not expect another Counter Strike from Troika (and I'd hope it doesn't end up being anything like it).
